    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hey. \n\nSo I think this is a place where the spec is slightly ambiguous and more guidance should be provided to implementers.  From that same section\n\n\"Clients  that generate HTTP/2 requests directly SHOULD use the \":authority\"  pseudo-header field instead of the \"Host\" header field.\"\n\nwhich is the case here. What the spec does not say anything about is an intermediary converting from HTTP/1.1 to HTTP2 though my read is that it should conform to the above and MUST convert Host->:authority given that Host is always present in HTTP/1.1\n\nHave you seen any clarification on this from the spec group.\n\nFYI - Nice work on nghttp!\n"
  },
