    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "My understanding is that \"Client that generate HTTP/2 request directly...\" is meant for endpoint that generates requests for their own (e.g., web browser).   This excludes intermediaries which forward requests on behalf of upstream clients.\nSo web browser is a client that generate HTTP/2 request directly, so it use \":authority\" and can omit host entirely.\nOTOH, intermediaries forward HTTP/1 request with origin-form to HTTP/2 link, MUST omit \":authority\" and use \"host\" header field.\n"
